PRETORIA - Opposition parties were out in force on the Day of Action in Pretoria on Wednesday in a mass display of unprecedented unity against the leadership of President Zuma.EFF Leader Julius Malema used the occasion to label ANC MP's as cowards."Members of the ANC in Parliament, we know you are cowards, I worked with all of you, you are cowards, I know all of you, I worked with all of them, they are cowards, but don't worry we are arranging so you are not exposed. Gen Holomisa is making arrangements so you are not exposed for those cowards of the ANC, so that they can do it secretly without their masters knowing. So cowards of the ANC we've got you covered," said Malema.WATCH: Opposition leaders address National Day Of Action protestersMalema said he was still hoping for a secret ballot during Parliament's Motion of No Confidence in President Zuma, at present scheduled to take place on 18 April.* View photos of the event in the gallery above. eNCA